I never imagined that VR could be this. It was surreal, sad and beautiful. I was able to take a seat, right across from Van gogh and catch a tiny glimpse of what it must've been like to see France through his eyes.

A definite experience for all.
Just realize there isn't much to do other than explore and listen to the music.  Still, I think it's worth it to experience.
Music was nice, but this was to boring for me.

I saw the movie Loving Vincent, and this is just amazing I strongly suggest this
A beautiful VR experience, just having the abilitry to explore the painted cafe would have been enough, but watching Van Gogh move and interact with his world was an amazing experience.

As a one-off experience, it is something very special indeed. To be able to jump into the paintings and maybe see the world through his own eyes might sound like an off app to create. But yet, somehow it works and you end up with one of the most beautiful art apps ever made. Van Gogh is a great choice for a VR app art style. Take a moment to enjoy his iconic sunflowers in 3 dimensions or walk around the chair he painted in his bedroom to see it from another angle. Step into the vivid colors straight from his palette of this impressionist world.

Positional tracking allows me to walk out into the patio, take a seat, and stare at the night sky while listening to the piano. absolutely marvelous! I really like the Gear VR experience when it first came out, but this is a whole new level.
Everyone I show this to in VR is very impressed, as I am myself.  Can't go wrong with this one.
As ever, a great introductory experience.
